Job Description:
Are you a strategic thinker? Do you enjoy corralling information, collaborating with a diverse group of stakeholders and content owners, and bringing a new vision to reality? Are you interested in helping NASA improve the way it serves users of NASA science data? If so, this is a new opportunity for you.

Science Systems and Applications, Inc. is looking to hire an experienced content strategist to join a web strategy and communications team that is responsible for improving the experience of users who are seeking to discover, download, and use NASA science data.

This position will require you to develop and implement content strategies with the goal of improving the use of science data. You will be working within an environment of content owners and stakeholders and navigating that environment will require managing divergent opinions while at the same time maintaining firm focus on the project vision.

This position is 100% virtual/telework. You will be working within a virtual team and will be required to conduct business within that virtual environment, including both audio- and video-based collaboration. In addition, this group will need to initiate contact and collaborate with other geographically dispersed teams within NASA. As such, this position requires active communication in order to maintain working relationships.

Occasional travel may be required (about 5%).

In this position you will:
Work from broad goals to develop and execute a specific strategy;
Audit, evaluate, and consolidate existing content;
Develop editorial processes and workflows necessary to ensure that content stays up to date, is coherently crafted, and logically presented;
Author content (a mix of descriptive and technical writing) as necessary;
Evaluate analytics for providing input and result metrics;
Develop working-level knowledge of NASA science data systems;
Work with subject matter experts within science, technology, and information management.
Required Qualifications:
Bachelor’s Degree in communications, library science, journalism, information systems or related field and 5 years professional experience developing and executing content strategies for web or equivalent combination of education and experience.
An interest and passion for helping users find and use NASA science data;
Technical/web writing and editing experience;
Experience working in collaboration with other teams;
A proactive self-starter, showing initiative;
Ability to work and interact within a virtual team;
Ready and willing to undertake strategic challenges.
Understanding of science concepts;
Experience using science data
US Citizenship required.
** Please include a cover letter with your resume describing your relevant professional experience and how it may apply to this project. **

Desired Qualifications:
Experience maintaining a website using a content management systems (CMS);
Project management;
Understanding of taxonomies, ontologies, and information architecture (IA);
Experience using SmartSheets or a related tool for maintaining an editorial calendar that can be shared across multiple teams;
Experience with UX design, user research, and interface design is a plus.
Experience using NASA science data.
EOE, including disability/vets
Physical Requirements: While performing the duties of this job, the employee is regularly required to stand, walk, and use hands to touch, handle or feel objects, tools or controls. The employee frequently is required to talk and hear and occasionally required to reach with hands and arms and stoop, kneel, crouch, or crawl. Must regularly lift and/or move up to 10 pounds, and occasionally lift and/or move up to 25 pounds. Specific vision abilities required by this job include close vision, peripheral vision, depth perception and the ability to adjust focus.

